ss="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1711632530438"><lt-highlighter contenteditable="false" class="lt--mac-os" data-lt-linked="1" style="display: none; z-index: auto !important;"><lt-div spellcheck="false" class="lt-highlighter__wrapper" style="width: 593.328px !important; height: 313.469px !important; transform: none !important; transform-origin: 296.664px 156.734px !important; zoom: 1 !important;"><lt-div class="lt-highlighter__scroll-element" style="top: 0px !important; left: 0px !important; width: 593px !important; height: 313px !important;"><canvas class="lt-highlighter__canvas" width="58" height="21" style="display: none; top: 46px !important; left: 115px !important;"></canvas></lt-div></lt-div></lt-highlighter><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf_gs-text-paragraph-1 gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-justify-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-lt-tmp-id="lt-91640" spellcheck="false" data-gramm="false" data-exc=""><p></p><p><br></p><p></p><p><span style="color: inherit; font-family: inherit; font-size: inherit; text-align: inherit; letter-spacing: 0px; background-color: var(--body_bg);">Exfoliating is like a mini spa day for your skin, helping to whisk away those pesky dead cells that can make your skin look dull and dry in the winter. But here's the deal: don't get too carried away with it.&nbsp;</span></p><p><span style="color: inherit; font-family: inherit; font-size: inherit; text-align: inherit; letter-spacing: 0px; background-color: var(--body_bg);"><br></span></p><p><span style="color: inherit; font-family: inherit; font-size: inherit; text-align: inherit; letter-spacing: 0px; background-color: var(--body_bg);">Too much exfoliation, especially for dry skin, can turn the anticipated spa day into a bit of a buzzkill. </span><span style="color: inherit; font-family: inherit; font-size: inherit; text-align: inherit; letter-spacing: 0px; background-color: rgba(183, 227, 255, 0.25);">Over-exfoliating has the potential to irritate your skin</span><span style="color: inherit; font-family: inherit; font-size: inherit; text-align: inherit; letter-spacing: 0px; background-color: var(--body_bg);">, leaving it feeling more sensitive and exacerbating dryness.</span></p><p><span style="color: inherit; font-family: inherit; font-size: inherit; text-align: inherit; letter-spacing: 0px; background-color: var(--body_bg);"><br></span></p><p><span style="color: inherit; font-family: inherit; font-size: inherit; text-align: inherit; letter-spacing: 0px; background-color: var(--body_bg);">To maintain the delicate balance, opt for a gentle exfoliator that pampers rather than punishes your skin.</span><span style="color: inherit; font-family: inherit; font-size: inherit; text-align: inherit; letter-spacing: 0px; background-color: rgba(183, 227, 255, 0.25);"> Aim for a once or twice-a-week rendezvous with exfoliation</span><span style="color: inherit; font-family: inherit; font-size: inherit; text-align: inherit; letter-spacing: 0px; background-color: var(--body_bg);"> – just enough to keep your skin radiant without unleashing any unnecessary drama. This mindful approach ensures your skin receives the benefits without the risk of irritation, allowing it to breathe and rejuvenate naturally.</span></p><p><span style="color: inherit; font-family: inherit; font-size: inherit; text-align: inherit; letter-spacing: 0px; background-color: var(--body_bg);"><br></span></p><p><span style="color: inherit; font-family: inherit; font-size: inherit; text-align: inherit; letter-spacing: 0px; background-color: var(--body_bg);"><strong>Our top picks for gentle winter exfoliators are:&nbsp;</strong></span></p><p></p><p></p><p></p></div></div><div data-label="Row" data-key="row" data-atomgroup="row" id="r-1711632530382" class="gf_row" data-icon="gpicon-row" data-id="1711632530382" data-layout-lg="6+6" data-extraclass="" data-layout-md="6+6" data-layout-sm="6+6" data-layout-xs="12+12" style=""><div class="gf_column g