ant; height: 26px !important;"></lt-div></lt-div></lt-highlighter><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs gf-elm-left-lg" data-gemlang="en" data-exc="" data-lt-tmp-id="lt-5051" spellcheck="false" data-gramm="false"><h2 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2"><b>Keep Your Lips Moisturised</b></h2><div><b><br></b></div></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1711632530442" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1711632530442"><lt-highlighter contenteditable="false" class="lt--mac-os" data-lt-linked="1" style="display: none; z-index: auto !important;"><lt-div spellcheck="false" class="lt-highlighter__wrapper" style="width: 593.328px !important; height: 313.469px !important; transform: none !important; transform-origin: 296.664px 156.734px !important; zoom: 1 !important;"><lt-div class="lt-highlighter__scroll-element" style="top: 0px !important; left: 0px !important; width: 593px !important; height: 313px !important;"><canvas class="lt-highlighter__canvas" width="58" height="21" style="display: none; top: 46px !important; left: 115px !important;"></canvas></lt-div></lt-div></lt-highlighter><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf_gs-text-paragraph-1 gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-justify-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-lt-tmp-id="lt-91640" spellcheck="false" data-gramm="false" data-exc=""><p></p><p></p><p>Winter can be particularly unkind to our lips, often leaving them feeling dry, cracked, and uncomfortably chapped. As the colder temperatures set in, the air tends to be drier, and harsh winds can further strip away the natural moisture from our skin, including the delicate skin on our lips. To ensure that your lips remain soft, smooth, and supple throughout the colder months, prioritizing miniaturization becomes an essential aspect of your winter skincare routine.</p><p><br></p><p>Look for products that contain nourishing ingredients like <span style="background-color: rgba(183, 227, 255, 0.25);">beeswax, shea butter, coconut oil, or cocoa butter</span>. These ingredients provide a protective barrier, sealing in moisture and preventing the harsh winter elements from taking a toll on your lips.</p><p><br></p><p>Consider incorporating <span style="background-color: rgba(183, 227, 255, 0.25);">gentle exfoliation</span> into your lip care routine to remove any dry, flaky skin.</p><p></p><p>Exfoliating your lips once or twice a week helps enhance the effectiveness of your lip balm by allowing it to penetrate more deeply into the skin.</p><p><br></p><p>Winter lip tip: Avoid the temptation to lick your lips, as saliva can contribute to increased dryness. Instead, make a habit of applying lip balm regularly to keep your lips moisturised and prevent further discomfort. With these simple steps, you can ensure your lips stay comfortable and well-nourished throughout the winter.</p><p><br></p><p><span style="font-weight: bold;">Our winter lip care product picks are:&nbsp;</span></p><p><br></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p></div></div><div data-label="Row" data-key="row" data-atomgroup="row" id="r-1711632530486" class="gf_row" data-icon="gpicon-row" data-id="1711632530486" data-layout-lg="6+6" data-extraclass="" data-layout-md="6+6" data-layout-sm="6+6" data-layout-xs="12+12" style=""><div class="gf_column gf_col-lg-6 gf_col-md-6 gf_col-sm-6 gf_col-xs-12" id="c-1653642484175" data-id="1653642484175"><div data-label="Product" data-key="product" data-atomgroup="product" id="m-1711632530370" class="module-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-product" data-ver="3.1" data-id="1711632530370" data-assigned-ver="4" style="min-height: auto;"><div class="module" data-variant="auto" style="" data-current-variant="3972409088422